  "texts": [
    "The \"black box\" is not only found within the algorithms but also in the exploitative processes that often bind the poorest part of the world to make us believe that these processes are automated-but they are not.",
    "The demand for human labor to produce the datasets needed to run these Large Language Models grows exponentially.",
    "As a result, national and international institutions need to start asking questions quickly, in order to bring answers and a clear legislative framework for these new \"data labeler-proletarians.\"",
    "Finally, the issue related to language is, in my opinion, one of the thorniest to deal with.",
    "Aside from the concealed hypocrisy found among the AGI pioneers, who sell their products as being \"universal,\" the problem here is structural."
  ],
